 UNITED States’ National Basketball Association (NBA) superstar Jusuf Nurkic, 28, and his wife Emina Duric have arrived at Serengeti National Park for a three-day visit. A statement shared on Saturday by Tanzania National Parks (TANAPA)’s Senior Assistant Conservation Commissioner- Corporate Communications Mr Pascal Shelutete said the couple landed in the country on Friday, ready to experience the amazing atmosphere at the park. Jusuf, best known as ‘The Bosnian Beast’, is a Bosnian professional basketball player for the Portland Trail Blazers of the National Basketball Association (NBA) and he also represents the Bosnia and Herzegovina national team internationally. At the Serengeti Park, the couple will enjoy to see endless plains filled with exhilarating wildlife, the great wildebeest migration path and world class safari lodges.  